HEADWORD: Sortilege
<hw>Sor"ti*lege</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sortil⟦egrave⟧ge</ets>, fr. L. <ets>sors</ets>, <ets>sortis</ets>,
a lot + <ets>legere</ets> to gather, to select.]</ety> <def>The act or
practice of drawing lots; divination by drawing lots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A woman infamous for <qex>sortileges</qex> and witcheries.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sortilegious</ent>⟦br⟧
